  "doc_id": "22252",
  "text": "Here, we show that in the absence of TCF-1, pre-TCR-dependent initiation of cycling is dissociated from survival. Because TCF-1 is a nuclear effector of the canonical wnt signaling pathway, this raised the possibility that pre-TCR and wnt signaling had to cooperate to ensure thymocyte survival at the pre-TCR stage. In support of this notion, an increase in TCF/catenin signaling in vivo coincided with pre-TCR signaling. Because the activity of this reporter indicates a high level of wnt/catenin/TCF signaling, [CITATION_1] our data strongly suggest that the nuclear response to wnt signaling depends on the presence of a pre-TCR.",
